The courtyard opens wider

00:21:57.600 --> 00:21:59.720
Than it looked in the printed square

00:21:59.800 --> 00:22:02.200
A bike bell rings behind us

00:22:02.280 --> 00:22:05.100
And scatters the afternoon air

00:22:05.180 --> 00:22:07.520
You fold the map uneven

00:22:07.760 --> 00:22:10.140
I hold the edge from the wind

00:22:10.220 --> 00:22:12.400
The building numbers blur out

00:22:12.480 --> 00:22:15.380
Then settle themselves again

00:22:15.460 --> 00:22:17.800
Tilt the map till north sits level

00:22:17.880 --> 00:22:20.500
Fold the square, loosen the stress

00:22:20.580 --> 00:22:22.300
If the arrows trade their place

00:22:22.380 --> 00:22:26.200
I can read it on your face

00:22:36.260 --> 00:22:40.280
Past the fountain, past the green

00:22:40.820 --> 00:22:44.320
Past the benches we had not seen

00:22:44.920 --> 00:22:48.380
You tilt the campus
toward the courtyard

00:22:48.460 --> 00:22:52.420
I find the step I counted wrong

00:22:53.580 --> 00:22:58.900
The seminar hall is closer

00:22:58.980 --> 00:23:01.080
Than either of us had guessed

00:23:01.160 --> 00:23:03.460
Your thumb rests over the legend

00:23:03.540 --> 00:23:06.420
Mine keeps the crease compressed

00:23:06.740 --> 00:23:09.160
We arrive with our
notes still scattered

00:23:09.240 --> 00:23:11.380
And a laugh we try to spend

00:23:11.460 --> 00:23:14.240
The map stays folded sideways

00:23:14.320 --> 00:23:16.860
Like the afternoon can bend again

00:23:16.940 --> 00:23:19.460
Angle the map till numbers line

00:23:19.540 --> 00:23:21.920
Fold the square, loosen the stress

00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:24.020
If we miss the fastest line

00:23:24.100 --> 00:23:27.960
We still learn where fountains shine

00:24:04.800 --> 00:24:08.980
Your notebook opens beside my notes

00:24:10.400 --> 00:24:14.720
Two headings lean in careful rows

00:24:16.040 --> 00:24:19.340
You shade a box, then lift the lead

00:24:20.000 --> 00:24:23.720
Before the thought is oversaid

00:24:25.920 --> 00:24:29.260
The lecture drifts
through ceiling vents

00:24:31.260 --> 00:24:34.720
I copy less of every tense

00:24:34.800 --> 00:24:40.860
Your pencil pauses at the side

00:24:41.480 --> 00:24:50.070
Where blank space learns to hide

00:24:51.190 --> 00:24:54.410
Leave the edge unfilled

00:24:54.880 --> 00:25:00.010
Let the white space hold still

00:25:00.560 --> 00:25:05.950
Some thoughts arrive too early

00:25:06.230 --> 00:25:11.170
Some stay better until

00:25:11.910 --> 00:25:15.050
You underline the reading date

00:25:15.130 --> 00:25:18.170
Then tap the desk and hesitate

00:25:18.250 --> 00:25:20.610
I fold my sleeve above the ink

00:25:20.690 --> 00:25:23.730
And give the open place to think

00:25:23.810 --> 00:25:26.650
A corner curls from borrowed rain

00:25:26.730 --> 00:25:29.450
Your graph bends toward mine again

00:25:29.530 --> 00:25:32.250
We trade a look, then trade it back

00:25:32.330 --> 00:25:35.050
The margin keeps its open track

00:25:35.130 --> 00:25:37.290
Between two headings

00:25:38.290 --> 00:25:39.870
There is space

00:25:40.590 --> 00:25:42.710
Between two breaths

00:25:43.390 --> 00:25:45.290
A careful place

00:25:45.370 --> 00:25:49.290
You do not have to write it down

00:25:49.370 --> 00:25:51.650
I do not have to turn around

00:25:51.730 --> 00:25:54.050
The class can keep

00:25:54.410 --> 00:25:58.310
What we almost found

00:25:58.750 --> 00:26:02.210
Leave the edge unfilled

00:26:02.650 --> 00:26:07.770
Let the white space hold still

00:26:08.290 --> 00:26:13.510
Some thoughts arrive too early

00:26:14.110 --> 00:26:19.150
Some stay better until

00:26:19.630 --> 00:26:25.370
Notebook margin, left blank

00:26:26.630 --> 00:26:30.510
A pencil waits, unpressed

00:26:31.570 --> 00:26:36.170
The unsaid sits beside the work

00:26:36.630 --> 00:26:41.690
And asks no more of the rest

00:27:05.820 --> 00:27:10.480
Last row packs in a paper rush

00:27:10.560 --> 00:27:15.540
Chair legs scrape,
then the hallway hush

00:27:15.620 --> 00:27:19.900
By the board where
the stairwell starts

00:27:20.680 --> 00:27:24.880
You press one pin through
a loose green chart

00:27:26.340 --> 00:27:31.220
I read the edge while
you smooth it flat

00:27:32.140 --> 00:27:35.640
Study circle, date moved late

00:27:35.720 --> 00:27:41.560
Your backpack zipper
keeps a crooked beat

00:27:41.700 --> 00:27:45.440
My straight-walk habit
slips at your feet

00:27:45.760 --> 00:27:50.660
I had the main hall fixed in my head

00:27:51.100 --> 00:27:55.500
You choose the stairs
by the poster thread

00:27:55.760 --> 00:28:00.720
Two floors down, the crowd thins out

00:28:00.800 --> 00:28:05.920
I learn the stairwell you think about

00:28:06.240 --> 00:28:11.380
If the notice leans, I lean too

00:28:12.300 --> 00:28:16.260
Only keeping pace with you

00:28:16.980 --> 00:28:21.180
Past the board, the handrail shines

00:28:21.960 --> 00:28:49.620
An errand takes its time

00:28:49.700 --> 00:28:53.420
Someone laughs by the vending row

00:28:53.660 --> 00:28:58.560
Your sleeve catches the paper bow

00:28:59.000 --> 00:29:03.740
You tap the pin till the corner stays

00:29:03.820 --> 00:29:08.840
Then point your chin
toward the longer way

00:29:08.920 --> 00:29:13.600
The lab would be quicker west

00:29:13.680 --> 00:29:17.480
But the stairs miss most of the rest

00:29:17.560 --> 00:29:24.220
So I tuck my shortcut under my tongue

00:29:24.780 --> 00:29:28.180
And the extra minute runs

00:29:28.600 --> 00:29:33.480
If the notice leans, I lean too

00:29:34.600 --> 00:29:38.340
Only keeping pace with you

00:29:39.140 --> 00:29:43.300
Past the board, the handrail shines

00:29:43.720 --> 00:30:06.200
An errand takes its time

00:30:06.280 --> 00:30:09.760
Half a floor above the noise

00:30:09.840 --> 00:30:15.580
You stop before the final choice

00:30:15.660 --> 00:30:20.660
The posted sheet
keeps fluttering there

00:30:20.780 --> 00:30:26.200
A green square shaking
in the stairwell air

00:30:26.560 --> 00:30:32.240
If the notice leans, I lean too

00:30:32.320 --> 00:30:37.320
One more landing, window-blue

00:30:38.400 --> 00:30:42.360
Past the board, the handrail shines

00:30:42.860 --> 00:30:47.700
An errand takes its time

00:31:18.360 --> 00:31:20.780
Projector cord across the floor

00:31:20.860 --> 00:31:23.560
Black curve running
from desk to board

00:31:23.640 --> 00:31:26.260
People drift with
their notebooks high

00:31:26.340 --> 00:31:29.240
You catch the trip in
the corner of your eye

00:31:29.320 --> 00:31:32.060
You kneel by the cart,
then loop it back

00:31:32.140 --> 00:31:34.900
Behind the table, along the track

00:31:34.980 --> 00:31:37.380
A strip of tape pins the cord down

00:31:37.460 --> 00:31:40.320
And nobody asks why
the curve moved round

00:31:40.400 --> 00:31:43.180
I stack the printouts, miss my cue

00:31:43.260 --> 00:31:45.980
Watching the cart
settle because of you

00:31:46.060 --> 00:31:48.760
The screen hums on,
the first group starts

00:31:48.840 --> 00:31:52.780
You fix the space
without a word or nod

00:31:52.860 --> 00:31:56.020
You tape the black curve down

00:31:56.100 --> 00:31:58.860
Before the first group turns around

00:31:58.940 --> 00:32:02.940
The floor holds steady where we pass

00:32:03.020 --> 00:32:07.080
A plain repair beneath the class

00:32:08.080 --> 00:32:11.900
Chairs slide sideways, bags tuck in

00:32:11.980 --> 00:32:14.360
The laptop fan starts whispering

00:32:14.440 --> 00:32:16.860
You coil the slack by the metal leg

00:32:16.940 --> 00:32:20.040
Then nod to the group
at the table edge

00:32:20.120 --> 00:32:22.840
I pass the notes from row to row

00:32:22.920 --> 00:32:26.160
The title loads in a pale gray box

00:32:26.240 --> 00:32:28.220
You check the tape
with your sneaker toe

00:32:28.300 --> 00:32:31.700
Then fade back into
the classroom talk

00:32:31.920 --> 00:32:34.980
You tape the black curve down

00:32:35.120 --> 00:32:37.960
Before the first group turns around

00:32:38.060 --> 00:32:42.020
The floor holds steady where we pass

00:32:42.280 --> 00:32:45.960
A plain repair beneath the class

00:32:47.560 --> 00:32:50.580
Then the floor changes shape

00:32:50.660 --> 00:32:53.460
A taped-down curve, a steadier way

00:32:53.540 --> 00:32:56.040
The aisle keeps moving, side by side

00:32:56.120 --> 00:32:58.720
While the black cord
stays out of stride

00:32:58.800 --> 00:33:01.820
The slide clicks in,
the speaker breathes

00:33:01.900 --> 00:33:04.200
Your taped-down work
sits under the scene

00:33:04.280 --> 00:33:06.720
I almost say what I understand

00:33:06.800 --> 00:33:22.060
Then pass the next sheet as planned

00:33:22.140 --> 00:33:25.060
You tape the black curve down

00:33:25.140 --> 00:33:27.860
Before the first group turns around

00:33:27.940 --> 00:33:32.040
The floor holds steady where we pass

00:33:32.460 --> 00:33:36.140
A plain repair beneath the class

00:33:36.220 --> 00:33:40.660
The cord lies flat by the table leg

00:33:40.740 --> 00:33:45.900
And the class goes on because of it

00:34:13.180 --> 00:34:16.720
Last slide before dismissal

00:34:16.960 --> 00:34:19.780
Blue-gray screen at the front

00:34:19.860 --> 00:34:22.360
Bullet points lose their edges

00:34:22.440 --> 00:34:25.420
While the ceiling fans hum

00:34:25.500 --> 00:34:28.840
You copy only the heading

00:34:28.920 --> 00:34:30.980
Then leave the rest undone

00:34:31.300 --> 00:34:34.060
I circle half a sentence

00:34:34.140 --> 00:34:37.240
And forget the second one

00:34:37.320 --> 00:34:40.100
The lecturer says review the chart

00:34:40.180 --> 00:34:42.800
Your pencil rests,
mine misses the mark

00:34:42.880 --> 00:34:45.700
The class is packing into sound

00:34:45.780 --> 00:34:49.140
But the thought will not settle down

00:34:49.220 --> 00:34:52.080
The sentence started opening

00:34:52.160 --> 00:34:54.640
Right before the screen went dark

00:34:54.720 --> 00:34:57.620
If I turned before the cursor

00:34:57.700 --> 00:35:00.380
Would you read the other part

00:35:00.460 --> 00:35:03.480
The projector kept on humming

00:35:03.560 --> 00:35:06.260
As the final bullet blurred

00:35:06.340 --> 00:35:10.280
When the final slide begins to fade

00:35:10.360 --> 00:35:17.760
I keep the ending blurred

00:35:17.840 --> 00:35:20.900
Someone zips up a jacket

00:35:20.980 --> 00:35:23.320
Someone laughs by the aisle

00:35:23.400 --> 00:35:26.680
You line your notes by chapter

00:35:26.760 --> 00:35:29.320
Then look over for a while

00:35:29.400 --> 00:35:31.680
I ask about the reading

00:35:31.760 --> 00:35:34.860
You answer what we need

00:35:34.940 --> 00:35:38.280
But something in the spacing

00:35:38.480 --> 00:35:40.860
Says more than either sheet

00:35:40.940 --> 00:35:43.560
The cursor blinks, the cables hum

00:35:43.640 --> 00:35:46.500
The last few minutes come undone

00:35:46.580 --> 00:35:49.340
I breathe as if the bell might know

00:35:49.420 --> 00:35:52.740
Which line to keep and which to slow

00:35:52.940 --> 00:35:55.660
The sentence started opening

00:35:55.740 --> 00:35:58.220
Right before the screen went dark

00:35:58.300 --> 00:36:01.200
If I turned before the cursor

00:36:01.280 --> 00:36:04.000
Would you read the other part

00:36:04.080 --> 00:36:06.860
The projector kept on humming

00:36:06.940 --> 00:36:09.880
As the final bullet blurred

00:36:09.960 --> 00:36:13.900
When the final slide begins to fade

00:36:13.980 --> 00:36:17.020
I keep the ending blurred

00:36:17.100 --> 00:36:21.920
All the chairs begin to turn

00:36:22.000 --> 00:36:24.780
All the practiced phrases thin

00:36:24.860 --> 00:36:27.500
You ask if I am heading east

00:36:27.580 --> 00:36:30.540
I say I have a minute free

00:36:30.620 --> 00:36:33.020
The screen goes dim across your face

00:36:33.100 --> 00:36:36.020
The class lets go of its last place

00:36:36.100 --> 00:36:39.260
I want to ask, but breathe instead

00:36:39.340 --> 00:36:42.780
And carry half the thought ahead

00:36:43.500 --> 00:36:49.320
The sentence started—

00:36:49.400 --> 00:36:50.700
Almost—

00:36:50.780 --> 00:36:53.660
The screen goes dark

00:36:54.000 --> 00:36:57.220
And the rest stays

00:37:23.800 --> 00:37:26.660
Window latch after class

00:37:26.740 --> 00:37:30.240
A silver click; the crosswind stills

00:37:30.320 --> 00:37:32.280
You check the frame and step aside

00:37:32.360 --> 00:37:36.160
Like ordinary work can stay

00:37:36.240 --> 00:37:39.320
The board is clean,
two blinds hang low

00:37:39.400 --> 00:37:42.420
Two bags lift from different rows

00:37:42.500 --> 00:37:45.660
I watch the silence gather up

00:37:45.740 --> 00:37:48.780
The part I almost told

00:37:48.860 --> 00:37:51.320
Keep it unhurried

00:37:51.400 --> 00:37:53.860
Hallway moving slow

00:37:54.340 --> 00:37:58.380
If we go lightly through

00:37:58.680 --> 00:38:07.140
I can learn that too

00:38:07.220 --> 00:38:11.060
You set the eraser straight

00:38:11.140 --> 00:38:14.640
I stack the copies by the wall

00:38:15.160 --> 00:38:17.340
The late sun stripes the floor

00:38:17.420 --> 00:38:21.000
But it does not feel gone at all

00:38:21.240 --> 00:38:23.700
Your zipper answers mine

00:38:23.780 --> 00:38:27.000
A simple sound across the aisle

00:38:27.080 --> 00:38:30.540
We do not seal the story here

00:38:30.620 --> 00:38:33.240
The last light rests awhile

00:38:33.320 --> 00:38:35.820
Keep it unhurried

00:38:35.900 --> 00:38:38.340
Hallway moving slow

00:38:38.660 --> 00:38:42.920
If we go lightly through

00:38:43.640 --> 00:38:48.200
I can learn that too

00:38:48.780 --> 00:38:53.440
Lower now, the campus hum

00:38:53.560 --> 00:38:56.540
Footsteps pass, then fewer come

00:38:56.620 --> 00:39:00.700
The latch is set,
the blinds are square

00:39:01.280 --> 00:39:05.880
Copies stacked beside my chair

00:39:05.960 --> 00:39:09.200
We close the frame and keep it there

00:39:09.280 --> 00:39:15.320
A daily task we both can share

00:39:16.360 --> 00:39:18.980
Keep it unhurried

00:39:19.060 --> 00:39:21.360
Hallway moving slow

00:39:21.820 --> 00:39:43.240
If we go—

00:39:43.320 --> 00:39:45.960
I can learn
